class ImageFolderDataset[source]

ImageFolderDataset(*args, **kwds) :: BaseClassificationDataset

Create Dataset instance from source using transforms

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Required arguments :

  • source: Union[str, Path] - Source directory of the Images
  • cfg: DictConfig - TRANSFORMS.{TRAIN/VALID} instance of lightning_cv.config.get_cfg

You can optinally pass in classes, which should be a Dict that contains a mapping of {class_name: interger_label} and test ; if not test, targets are not returned, only images are returned after applying tfm

Images should arranged in this way:

root/dog/xxx.png
root/dog/xxy.png
root/dog/xxz.png

root/cat/123.png
root/cat/nsdf3.png
root/cat/asd932_.png
{% raw %} 
cfg = get_cfg()
ds  = ImageFolderDataset(source=data_path, test=False, cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.TRAIN)
dl  = DataLoader(ds, batch_size=5, shuffle=True)

# since test is False both images and targets are returned
logger.info(f"Transformations Used : \n{ds.transforms}")
image, target = next(iter(dl))
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
imshow_tensor(image, normalize=True)

Transformations can also be changed after instantiating the Dataset class.

{% raw %} 
transforms = create_transform(cfg.TRANSFORMS.VALID)

logger.info(f"Transformations Used: \n{transforms.TRANSFORMS}")

ds.transforms = transforms.TRANSFORMS

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
image, target = next(iter(dl))
imshow_tensor(image, normalize=True)

Generating a Test Dataset (Dataset without test labels) :

{% raw %} 
ds = ImageFolderDataset(source=os.path.join(data_path, "cats"), cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.VALID, test=True)

dl = DataLoader(ds, batch_size=5, shuffle=True)

# since test is True only images are returned
image = next(iter(dl))
logger.info(f"Transformations Used : \n{ds.transforms}")
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
imshow_tensor(image, title="Test Images", normalize=True)

class ImageCsvDataset[source]

ImageCsvDataset(*args, **kwds) :: BaseClassificationDataset

Create Dataset instance from csv using transforms, image_col and label_col

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Arguments:

  • csv (str): path to the csv file.
  • cfg (DictConfig) - TRANSFORMS.{TRAIN/VALID} instance of lightning_cv.config.get_cfg
  • label_col (Optional[str]): name of the column where the labels for the images are stored.
  • loader (str): item in Loaders registery for reading the Images.
  • test (bool): if test , then only images are returned and label_col is skipped.
  • kwargs : arguments for pd.read_csv

Example -

{% raw %}
image_id target label
0 /Users/ayushman/Desktop/lightning_cv/nbs/data/cats_and_dogs_filtered/train/dogs/dog.85.jpg dogs 1
1 /Users/ayushman/Desktop/lightning_cv/nbs/data/cats_and_dogs_filtered/train/dogs/dog.665.jpg dogs 1
2 /Users/ayushman/Desktop/lightning_cv/nbs/data/cats_and_dogs_filtered/train/cats/cat.524.jpg cats 0

4 /Users/ayushman/Desktop/lightning_cv/nbs/data/cats_and_dogs_filtered/train/dogs/dog.90.jpg dogs 1
{% endraw %}

Let's create Dataset s and DataLoaders from the above csv file.

{% raw %} 
cfg = get_cfg()
csv = f"{data_path}/train.csv"

ds = ImageCsvDataset(csv, image_col="image_id", label_col="label", cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.TRAIN)

dl  = DataLoader(ds, batch_size=5, shuffle=True)
image, target = next(iter(dl))

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
imshow_tensor(image,normalize=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
csv  = f"{data_path}/train.csv"

ds = ImageCsvDataset(csv, image_col="image_id", label_col="label", cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.VALID, test=True)

dl = DataLoader(ds, batch_size=5, shuffle=True)

image = next(iter(dl))

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
imshow_tensor(image,normalize=True)

ClassificationDatasetCatalog

A _DatasetCatalog instance for ImageClassification Datasets.

{% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

DatasetCatalog(registered datasets: )[source]

A global dictionary that stores information about the datasets and how to obtain them. It contains a mapping from strings (which are names that identify a dataset, e.g. "my_dataset_train") to a function which parses the instanitiates the Dataset obj.

From - https://github.com/facebookresearch/detectron2/blob/master/detectron2/data/catalog.py

Methods: lightning_cv.classification.data.datasets.ClassificationDatasetCatalog.register lightning_cv.classification.data.datasets.ClassificationDatasetCatalog.get

create_dataset[source]

create_dataset(cfg:DictConfig)

Retrive a BaseClassificationDataset instance from ImageClassificationDatasetCatalog.

Note: This function retrives both the train and valid datasets from config. Ideally you want want both train and validation datsets but if you do not have a validation dataset, then set DATASETS.VALID = None

{% endraw %}

cfg = get_cfg()

# print(cfg.pretty())

# build datasets from config
train_dataset = lambda: ImageFolderDataset(source=train_path, cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.TRAIN)
valid_dataset = lambda: ImageFolderDataset(source=valid_path, cfg=cfg.TRANSFORMS.VALID)

# register datasets
ClassificationDatasetCatalog.register("my_train_dataset", train_dataset)
ClassificationDatasetCatalog.register("my_valid_dataset", valid_dataset)

# update config
cfg.DATASETS.TRAIN = "my_train_dataset"
cfg.DATASETS.VALID = "my_valid_dataset"
